[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       1243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - *Privacy-team routing.* The privacy team has explicit federation-equity-evaluation authority. Disparity alerts route to both the analytics-governance committee and the privacy team. The privacy team evaluates whether the disparity constitutes a framework-equity concern (cohort disparities at federation scale are simultaneously fairness signals and framework-compliance signals).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       1244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - *Framework-equity translation.* Cohort disparities at federation scale map to TEFCA's participation requirements. Persistent cohort disparities above the institutional threshold are reported to the QHIN as a framework-equity concern and may trigger the QHIN's cross-participant coordination process.
